cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.AI 

This paper deals with the design of a communication system for millimeter-wave vehicular networks that takes into account the mobility of users and the dynamics of blockages. The problem is formulated as a partially observable Markov decision process, which suggests that the paper could belong to the sub-categories of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) or cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also proposes an approximate dynamic programming algorithm, which involves optimization techniques, indicating that it could belong to the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper deals with the optimization of throughput and power consumption, which suggests that it could belong to the sub-category of cs.IT (Information Theory). Finally, the paper specifically focuses on millimeter-wave vehicular networks, which suggests that it could belong to the sub-category of cs.MM (Multimedia).
